 {"id":"bd-1oy","title":"Task: Implement daemon core with UDS listener and protocol","description":"## Task: Implement Daemon Core with Unix Domain Socket

Build the core daemon that keeps embedding/reranker models warm in memory,
accepting requests over a Unix Domain Socket with MessagePack serialization.

## Architecture

### Daemon Lifecycle
```
xf daemon start → fork+setsid → bind UDS → write PID → accept loop → idle timeout → shutdown
```

### Core Structure
```rust
pub struct ModelDaemon {
    socket_path: PathBuf,
    pid_path: PathBuf,
    models: ModelManager,
    config: DaemonConfig,
    idle_timeout: Duration,      // Default: 30 minutes
    last_request: Instant,
}

struct ModelManager {
    embedders: HashMap<String, Box<dyn Embedder>>,
    rerankers: HashMap<String, Box<dyn Reranker>>,
    registry: ModelRegistry,
    max_models: usize,           // From resource config
}

impl ModelManager {
    /// Lazy load: model loaded on first request, stays resident
    fn get_embedder(&mut self, name: &str) -> Result<&dyn Embedder> {
        if !self.embedders.contains_key(name) {
            if self.embedders.len() >= self.max_models {
                self.evict_lru();
            }
            let config = EmbedderConfig::from_name(name)?;
            let embedder = self.registry.embedder(&config)?;
            self.embedders.insert(name.to_string(), embedder);
        }
        Ok(self.embedders.get(name).unwrap().as_ref())
    }
}
```

### Protocol (MessagePack over UDS)
```rust
/// Envelope: [version: u8, id: u64, payload_bytes: Vec<u8>]
/// Version 1 protocol

#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct Envelope {
    pub version: u8,     // Always 1
    pub id: u64,         // Client request ID (for response correlation)
    pub payload: Vec<u8>, // MessagePack-encoded payload
}

#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub enum Request {
    Health,
    Embed {
        texts: Vec<String>,
        model: String,
        dims: Option<usize>,  // MRL truncation
    },
    Rerank {
        query: String,
        documents: Vec<String>,
        model: String,
    },
    Status,    // Returns loaded models, memory, uptime
    Shutdown,  // Graceful shutdown
}

#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub enum Response {
    Health { uptime_secs: u64, models_loaded: usize },
    Embeddings { vectors: Vec<Vec<f32>> },
    Scores { scores: Vec<f32> },
    Status {
        uptime_secs: u64,
        models: Vec<ModelInfo>,
        rss_mb: f64,
        requests_served: u64,
    },
    Error { code: u16, message: String },
    Shutdown { ok: bool },
}
```

### Connection Handling
```rust
async fn accept_loop(listener: UnixListener, daemon: Arc<Mutex<ModelDaemon>>) {
    loop {
        tokio::select! {
            Ok((stream, _)) = listener.accept() => {
                let daemon = Arc::clone(&daemon);
                tokio::spawn(async move {
                    handle_connection(stream, daemon).await;
                });
            }
            _ = idle_timeout_check(&daemon) => {
                info!("Idle timeout reached, shutting down");
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    cleanup(&daemon).await;
}

async fn handle_connection(mut stream: UnixStream, daemon: Arc<Mutex<ModelDaemon>>) {
    // Read length-prefixed MessagePack envelope
    let len = stream.read_u32().await?;
    let mut buf = vec![0u8; len as usize];
    stream.read_exact(&mut buf).await?;

    let envelope: Envelope = rmp_serde::from_slice(&buf)?;
    assert_eq!(envelope.version, 1, "Unsupported protocol version");

    let request: Request = rmp_serde::from_slice(&envelope.payload)?;
    let response = daemon.lock().await.handle_request(request).await;

    // Write response
    let resp_bytes = rmp_serde::to_vec(&response)?;
    let resp_envelope = Envelope { version: 1, id: envelope.id, payload: resp_bytes };
    let envelope_bytes = rmp_serde::to_vec(&resp_envelope)?;
    stream.write_u32(envelope_bytes.len() as u32).await?;
    stream.write_all(&envelope_bytes).await?;
}
```

### Idle Timeout
- Timer resets on every request
- Default: 30 minutes (configurable in daemon.toml)
- On timeout: log, unload models, remove socket + PID file, exit
- SIGTERM/SIGINT: same graceful shutdown path

### Socket Permissions
- Socket created with mode 0600 (owner-only)
- PID file: 0644

### Startup Sequence
1. Parse config from ~/.config/xf/daemon.toml
2. Apply nice/ionice/resource limits (bd-ld7m)
3. Bind UDS at /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.sock
4. Write PID to /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.pid
5. Install signal handlers (SIGTERM, SIGINT)
6. Enter accept loop
7. Log: "Daemon ready, PID={pid}, socket={path}"

